# Publishing your thesis

## Preparing for your submission
-[] Add line numbers to your thesis, to ensure that each line is numbered in order starting on the first page.

-[] High quality figures, preferably as vector graphics (eps or pdf).

-[] A cover letter outlining the impact of your work and highlighting the major outcomes.

## Revising your submission
Leave the submitted version as it is and copy it into a new version that will be a revision.  At the end of the process, we’ll compare the two version and make that the “tracked changes version”, highlighting all changes.

Copy all of the comments from the editors and three reviewers into a single word document called “response to reviews.





